headline: Grocery Stores Limit Egg Purchases. Why Shoppers Shouldn’t Panic.
summary: Egg prices rose another 15.2% in January, according to consumer price index data released on Wednesday.  Not only have shortages resulting from the spread of bird flu pushed prices higher, some grocery stores are limiting how many eggs a customer can buy.  This week, reports said  Costco Wholesale  and Trader Joe’s have set restrictions on egg purchases, while  Walmart  said its Sam’s Club stores while  Walmart  said its Sam’s Club stores also have a limit on buying.
